text: Artocarpus blancoi is a species of plant in the family Moraceae endemic to the Philippines. Its habitat (among seasonal forest or thicket growth in low-lying areas) is threatened. It is locally known as tipolo or antipolo by the Filipinos. Paper production and being a shade provider are its primary uses, although its seeds and fruits are edible. The City of Antipolo got its name from the said tree. ==See also== *Ginataang langka ==References== blancoi Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Plants described in 1923 Category:Flora of the Philippines Category:Endemic flora of the Philippines Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
